• Running a shortcut from another shortcut (using the Run Shortcut action). The output will be used as the output of the Run Shortcut action.
• Running a shortcut from Quick Actions in Finder on macOS. The output will be saved as a file alongside the files selected in Finder.
• Running a shortcut from Services on macOS. The output will replace the selected text, if applicable.
• Or, when running a shortcut from another location that supports output, like the command-line or the Shortcuts URL scheme.

No more actions will be run after this action.

is.workflow.actions.getarticle.name: Get Article using Safari Reader
is.workflow.actions.getarticle.description: Gets article details, including body text, author, publish date, and more, from every URL passed into the action.

is.workflow.actions.showdefinition.name: Show Definition
is.workflow.actions.showdefinition.description: Shows the definition of the word passed into the action.

is.workflow.actions.getdirections.name: Open Directions
is.workflow.actions.getdirections.description: Opens directions to the location passed into this action in your choice of Maps, Google Maps, Citymapper, Transit, or Waze. For example, you can use this action to get directions to an upcoming event on your calendar.

arguments.name: Sort by

is.workflow.actions.list.name: List
is.workflow.actions.list.description: Allows you to specify a list of items to be passed to the next action.

is.workflow.actions.detect.phonenumber.name: Get Phone Numbers from Input
is.workflow.actions.detect.phonenumber.description: Returns any phone numbers found in the output from the previous action.

is.workflow.actions.choosefrommenu.name: Choose from Menu
is.workflow.actions.choosefrommenu.description: Prompt the user with a list of menu items and run the matching branch.
notes: Each menu block uses the same `GroupingIdentifier`. Set `WFControlFlowMode` to 0 for the opening "Choose from Menu" action, 1 for each menu branch, and 2 for the final End Menu block.
Provide the list of choices via `WFMenuItems`, and optionally set `WFMenuPrompt` to customize the alert text shown to the user.

is.workflow.actions.repeat.count.name: Repeat
is.workflow.actions.repeat.count.description: Repeat the contained actions a specific number of times.
notes: Set `WFControlFlowMode` to 0 for the opening Repeat block and 1 for the closing End Repeat block. Both must share the same `GroupingIdentifier`.
Use `WFRepeatCount` to control how many times the actions run. Inside the loop you can use `Repeat Index` and `Repeat Item` magic variables.

is.workflow.actions.repeat.each.name: Repeat with Each
is.workflow.actions.repeat.each.description: Run the contained actions for every item passed into the loop.
notes: Opening and closing blocks share the same `GroupingIdentifier`. Set `WFControlFlowMode` to 0 for the opening Repeat with Each and 1 for the End Repeat block.
Use the `Repeat Item` magic variable inside the loop to access the current element, or `Repeat Index` for the position.

is.workflow.actions.conditional.name: If
is.workflow.actions.conditional.description: Branch based on conditions, optionally providing Otherwise and End If blocks.
notes: Use `WFControlFlowMode` 0 for the opening If, 1 for Otherwise, and 2 for End If. All related blocks must share the same `GroupingIdentifier`.
